<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-5654700/R-HSA-5654700>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> , <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0008150> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "The FRS family of scaffolding adaptor proteins has two members, FRS2 (also known as FRS2 alpha) and FRS3 (also known as FRS2beta or SNT-2). Activation of FGFR tyrosine kinase allows FRS proteins to become phosphorylated on tyrosine residues and then bind to the adaptor GRB2 and the tyrosine phosphatase PPTN11/SHP2. Subsequently, PPTN11 activates the RAS-MAP kinase pathway and GRB2 activates the RAS-MAP kinase , PI-3-kinase and ubiquitinations/degradation pathways by binding to SOS, GAB1 and CBL, respectively, via the SH3 domains of GRB2. FRS2 acts as a central mediator in FGF signaling mainly because it induces sustained levels of activation of ERK with ubiquitous expression.<br><br><br>" ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "FRS-mediated FGFR2 signaling" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "Reviewed: Gotoh, N, 2011-08-26" , "Edited: Jupe, S, 2010-02-03" , "Reviewed: Mohammadi, M, 2007-02-06 21:44:35" , "Authored: de Bono, B, 2007-01-10 10:27:18" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date>
                "2026-04-09" ;
        <http://purl.org/pav/providedBy>
                "https://reactome.org" ;
        <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref>
                "R-HSA-5654700" ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#narrower>
                <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-5654696/R-HSA-5654696> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note>
                "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

